<div style="text-align: center;"><img height="94" src="Images/housing/Student Living/Apartment Managers/owner-agreement.png" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" width="800" /><em>There are two specific statements referencing this requirement under "Landlord Obligations" in the Agreement to Provide </em></div>
<div style="text-align: center;"><em>BYU-Idaho Approved Housing. Please see below.</em></div>
<div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Management/supervision</strong>: Landlord agrees to provide on-site management and supervision as outlined in the Approved Housing Guidebook. Such management and supervision must include, among other things, the following:</p>
<p>1. Live the BYU-Idaho Honor Code in an exemplary fashion;</p>
<p>2. Attend and actively participate in all monthly training meetings sponsored by the Housing &amp; Student Living Office; complete "New Manager Orientation" within the first three months of service as a new manager; and participate in the annual Housing &amp; Student Living Professional Development Conference.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>General requirements:</strong> Landlord shall:</p>
<p>1. Provide an ecclesiastical endorsement annually for any and all on-site managers and spouses;</p>
<p>2. Require management to attend all training and development meetings sponsored by the Housing &amp; Student Living Office (see 3-B-2) as a condition to retain employment and maintain approved status in the BYU-Idaho approved housing market;</p>
